<br/>
<div class="mw-parser-output">
 <p>
  You can deploy the following containerized components of Operations Bridge Suite with Premium and Ultimate license editions on AWS.
 </p>
 <ul>
  <li>
   Business Value Dashboard
  </li>
  <li>
   COSO Data Lake
  </li>
  <li>
   Performance Management
  </li>
  <li>
   Digital Experience Monitoring
  </li>
  <li>
   Collection Services
  </li>
 </ul>
 <p>
  <br/>
  This document explains the installation and configuration of the Operations Bridge suite and you must perform the following steps in the given sequence:
 </p>
 <a class="buttonfullscr" onclick="javascript:loadingTableButton(this);">
  <button class="flscrbtn">
   <i class="material-icons flscricn">
    open_in_new
   </i>
   <div style="margin: auto 5px;">
    View Fullscreen
   </div>
  </button>
 </a>
 <table>
  <tbody>
   <tr>
    <td>
     <b>
      Phase
     </b>
    </td>
    <td>
     <b>
      Objective
     </b>
    </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td>
     Plan
    </td>
    <td>
     Create  a deployment plan and the resources required for the installation of  the containerized components by performing the following steps:
     <ol>
      <li>
       Deployment modes
      </li>
      <li>
       Support Matrix
      </li>
      <li>
       Sizing recommendations
      </li>
      <li>
       AWS region selection
      </li>
     </ol>
    </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td>
     Prepare
    </td>
    <td>
     Using the systems created in the Plan phase, prepare  and configure the AWS resources required for the installation of containerized components by performing the  following steps:
     <ol>
      <li>
       Activate Docker Hub account
      </li>
      <li>
       Prepare AWS resources
       <ul>
        <li>
         VPC
        </li>
        <li>
         Subnets
        </li>
        <li>
         NAT gateway
        </li>
        <li>
         EC2 instances
        </li>
        <li>
         Check connectivity
        </li>
        <li>
         Target group
        </li>
        <li>
         Network Load Balancer
        </li>
        <li>
         Application Load Balancer
        </li>
        <li>
         Amazon Route 53
        </li>
        <li>
         Database (Amazon RDS)
        </li>
        <li>
         Postgress RDS
        </li>
        <li>
         Oracle RDS
        </li>
        <li>
         Configure AWS EFS shares
        </li>
       </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
       Configure EC2 instances
      </li>
      <li>
       Configure EFS Storage
      </li>
      <li>
       (optional) Configure an NFS Server
      </li>
      <li>
       Download the installation Packages
      </li>
      <li>
       Configure installation permission for a sudo user
      </li>
      <li>
       Configure the install.properties file
      </li>
     </ol>
    </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td>
     Deploy
    </td>
    <td>
     Install, deploy, and configure containerized components in your  environment by performing the following steps:
     <ol>
      <li>
       Install CDF
      </li>
      <li>
       Select the deployment configuration
      </li>
      <li>
       Download the container images
      </li>
      <li>
       Deploy  and Configure Operations Bridge Suite
      </li>
      <li>
       Reconfigure Ingress Controller
      </li>
      <li>
       Verify the installation
      </li>
     </ol>
    </td>
   </tr>
  </tbody>
 </table>
